spanGrp.span: ‘I saw that a mother had a child in her hands, in a crib.
Yís sũã-ra yaba (_) í mina-wa yaba kate jula nã kunita nã
Then the father came and told her something;
Jeska í kaga deũ-te jirö she-gẽ ĩã
menẽtse í kaga wã í mina
There it seems that a creature stole the child;
Jeska í blá-wã juela bichi të
the creature stole him and took him where there are snakes, creatures and animals.
Bichi të í blá-wã kebé animal mãĩ jirö bichi tsõ ska animal tsõ
Jeska í menẽtse-mĩ í wã yaba damĩũ jeska
His mother came back home to look for him; his father thought that an animal had stolen him.
jekea mina deu-nẽ í yulö Í (m) kaga (_) je të begetsá rö-nã (_) ele… ke ani animal nẽ të í (m) blá-wã rö nẽ (m)
But it was the elves who stole him.’
Ñerö (_) dwende të í blá-wã yaba blá-wã
